CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 28, 1960, pg. 7, reads: "Withdraws Bias Case - Thomas Page, right, Carnegie tavern owner, is shown signing to dismiss the discrimination charge which he filed against another tavern owner, Dorothy Yoachim, in office of Alderman Harry B. Fitzgerald. Deputy Constable Fred Terry is shown on the left. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Thomas Page signing document in front of Deputy Constable Fred Terry, in office of Alderman Harry Fitzgerald
